panels.content:
In the graphs below following terms denote the following queue numbers:
Total The total number of the interactions in the queue
In Router The number of the interactions being routed. This metric is not available in Pulse.
On Agents The number of the interactions being handled by agents. This metric is not available in Pulse.
In Queue The number of the interactions waiting to be routed by routers and/or be handled by agents
Never Delivered to Agent The typical lifetime of interactions includes following steps:
  1. Received and submitted to queue
  2. Sent for routing
  3. (optional) Placed in another queue and sent for routing
  4. Handled by agent
  5. (optional) Placed in post-processing queue and sent for routing
  6. Stopped
Interaction is considered "never delivered" until it reaches agent in step 4.
In Router and On Agents The sum of the interactions being routed by routers and being handled by agents

Queue statistics below is available in Pulse for customers.
